  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM) and Direct Life-Saving Assistance for Conflict-Affected Populations in Eastern Democratic Republic of Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of the project is to provide humanitarian assistance to conflict-affected populations in spontaneous displacement sites and surrounding communities in the Democratic Republic of Congo. Activities under this project contribute towards a more informed and coordinated humanitarian response in displacement sites across the North-Kivu, Tanganyika and Ituri provinces, as well as improve the living conditions and protection of the most vulnerable internally displaced persons through improved site coordination and management.</narrative>
  </description>
